<li id="cite_note-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/life/story/0,6903,466391,00.html" class="external text" title="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/life/story/0,6903,466391,00.html" rel="nofollow">"Modern boys and mobile girls"</a>. <a href="/wiki/The_Observer" title="The Observer">The Observer</a>. <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="2001-04-01"><a href="/wiki/2001" title="2001">2001</a>-<a href="/wiki/April_1" title="April 1">04-01</a></span><span class="printonly">. <a href="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/life/story/0,6903,466391,00.html" class="external free" title="http://observer.guardian.co.uk/life/story/0,6903,466391,00.html" rel="nofollow">http://observer.guardian.co.uk/life/story/0,6903,466391,00.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Modern+boys+and+mobile+girls&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=%5B%5B2001-04-01%5D%5D&amp;rft.pub=%5B%5BThe+Observer%5D%5D&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fobserver.guardian.co.uk%2Flife%2Fstory%2F0%2C6903%2C466391%2C00.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Otaku"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web"><a href="http://www.gamespot.com/news/6142794.html" class="external text" title="http://www.gamespot.com/news/6142794.html" rel="nofollow">"Otakon clock to come with select MGS titles"</a>. GameSpot. 2006-01-20<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.gamespot.com/news/6142794.html" class="external free" title="http://www.gamespot.com/news/6142794.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.gamespot.com/news/6142794.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Otakon+clock+to+come+with+select+MGS+titles&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.date=2006-01-20&amp;rft.pub=GameSpot&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gamespot.com%2Fnews%2F6142794.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Otaku"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://paper.wenweipo.com/2008/09/23/GJ0809230014.htm" class="external text" title="http://paper.wenweipo.com/2008/09/23/GJ0809230014.htm" rel="nofollow">Otaku uses manga and anime to improve Foreign Affairs</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
