<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Otaku&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://waste.informatik.hu-berlin.de/Grassmuck/Texts/otaku.e.html" class="external text" title="http://waste.informatik.hu-berlin.de/Grassmuck/Texts/otaku.e.html" rel="nofollow">"I'm alone, but not lonely"</a> – an early article about Japanese otaku, December 1990</li>
<li><a href="http://www.cjas.org/~leng/otaku-p.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.cjas.org/~leng/otaku-p.htm" rel="nofollow">The Politics of Otaku</a> – a general commentary on the usage and meanings of "otaku" in Japan and internationally, September 2001</li>
<li><a href="http://otakuchic.com" class="external text" title="http://otakuchic.com" rel="nofollow">Otaku Chic</a> a site "dedicated to preserving Otaku culture."</li>
